{"key":"processedPost-3851144","value":{"id":3851144,"first":3849654,"last":3855333,"when":1109692771,"utime":"03/01/05 05:59 PM","content":"A 36 to 48 hour soak is fine.  The rye will stink to high heaven, but that's a good thing.  It means the bacterial endospores have germinated, so they'll be easily killed by the PC.  I always boil for five minutes in the water the grains soaked in to kill the live bacteria before dumping down the sink.  I don't want all that live bacteria going into the P-trap below my sink and thriving.","title":"Re: Rye Berries - Do not make this mistake"}}